bib.title: Shell and odd-even effects on alpha-particle energyspectra from the (p,alpha) reaction on nuclei aroundneutron number 50

free_txt: Data converted from EXFOR E1303. Numerical
data are exchanged with author's one. Many
To detect alpha-particle. Used as Delta E-E
having thickness of 15 and 300 micro-meter. The
energy scale for alpha-particles was calibrated
using the position of the alpha-particle peaks
leading to the ground states of the residual
nucleus for high energy calibration points. Low
energy calibration points were obtained using
the positions of the alpha-particle peaks
leading to low lying states of 13N in the
Beam intensity is 20 to 300 nA. (Smaller beam currents
were used at forward angles in order to reduce the
dead time for the detector system.)
